column20: Q8_For instructor:  [C$FN] [C$LN]What did you find to be most beneficial about the course?
column21: Q9_For instructor:  [C$FN] [C$LN]What would have made this course more effective for you?

column20: Reviewing and discussing research papers was incredibly valuable in strengthening my analysis and critical thinking skills. It not only improved my ability to assess academic work but also helped me articulate insights more clearly in group discussions. This focus on paper analysis was a key highlight for me.
column21: Overall, I’m mostly satisfied with the course. Adding more students could have created more discussion opportunities and diverse perspectives during paper reviews.

column12: We discussed everything on the syllabus and lots of other “tangents”
column13: Every single class was deep dive and discussions that helped me and taught how to develop and articulate my thoughts and opinions
column14: The professor got really excited every time I showed up during office hours
column19: One of the best professors I’ve had the opportunity to take a class with
column20: The really dynamic nature of the class with discussions and lectures taught me how to articulate and develop my thoughts
column21: Maybe some implementation related homeworks could help and solidify the theoretical concepts that were discussed in the class

column19: Jared was probably my favorite professor so far in the my experience here at LMU.
column20: The class discussion really forced you to take ownership and understand material.
column21: Great course, only wish we could have dived deeper into niche topics similar to the final project.

column20: I didn’t really know how to approach reading academic papers at first, so I struggled a bit in the beginning. However, learning how to read through a paper effectively and how to branch out from it to related topics has been a valuable lesson in itself. I’m truly grateful to the professor for that.
column21: Reading a wide range of papers and working on the final project were especially helpful for me. Although I still have a lot to learn, I believe this course provided meaningful direction for the rest of my master’s journey.
